//Congential heart disease - Atrial septal defect (ASD)


Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Cardio MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Congential heart disease' tab
Then 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Atrial septal defect (ASD)' from 'Congential heart disease' dropdown menu
Then 'Add pathology' button is enabled
And 'Ostium primum' radio button is enabled
And 'Ostium secundum' radio button is enabled
And 'Sinus venosus-type' radio button is enabled
And 'Sinus coronarius-type' radio button is enabled

And 'Cardiomegaly' checkbox is enabled
And 'RA / RV increase' checkbox is enabled
And 'Dilated pulmonary artery' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Sinus venosus-type' radio button
Then 'Vena cava superior-type' radio button is enabled
And 'Vena cava inferior-type' radio button is enabled
